The issue is due to IE7 (and IE6) not supporting &lt;tt&gt;inline-block&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;a class="attachment" href="http://localhost/attachment/ticket/1219/patch-1219-A0.diff" title="Attachment 'patch-1219-A0.diff' in Ticket #1219"&gt;patch-1219-A0.diff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a class="trac-rawlink" href="http://localhost/raw-attachment/ticket/1219/patch-1219-A0.diff" title="Download"&gt;​&lt;/a&gt; works around the issue.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
I'm reopening this ticket in case you want to consider my patch.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
But note that I won't be offended if you close it as wontfix again. I agree this is pretty minor, and that working around old browsers' limitations isn't always a good idea.
